Police and Correctional Services officials are searching for several awaiting-trial prisoners who escaped. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police and correctional services officials are searching for 8 awaiting-trial prisoners, who escaped in the Western Cape on Friday. A group of detainees overpowered officials at the Malmesbury Remand Detention Facility, during exercise time at around noon. COVID-19:Â Under 19,000 prisoners to be released on parole Correctional services say they took the prison officials' keys and locked three wardens in a cell. They then opened several other cells, and 69 escaped through the main entrance and over the roof. Police say 61 prisoners have been re-arrested. The prison is now under lockdown.